      <p class="- topic/p ">The key switch is a three position switch. Position (1) is
ACCESSORY OFF. Position (2) is On/Ignition.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">Position (3) is START, which engages the starter.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">After the key has been turned to the START position, the key
must be returned to the OFF position before it can be turned to the
START position again.</p>
